1.title: Camel Tow
1.plot: Rick and Andrew experience one of their toughest transports yet when moving an aggressive and dangerous European Bison in North Carolina.

2.title: Crouching Tiger, Hidden Cobra
2.plot: While transporting two Bengal tigers from Miami to South Carolina, Andrew is all about business while Rick's playful deception earns the duo some adorable extra cargo.

3.title: Chimp My Ride
3.plot: A road trip from Myrtle Beach to Miami gets "bananas" for Rick and Andrew when the chimpanzees they're transporting can't sit still, forcing them to come up with a new plan.

4.title: Crank Zedonks and Lemur Car Trip
4.plot: It's a race against the clock when Andrew and Rick run dangerously close to missing their deadline to deliver a veritable Noah's ark of cargo on a 900-mile trek to Mississippi. Meanwhile, Ashley steps up and shows Justin who's boss when it comes moving two difficult Zedonks into a larger enclosure.

6.title: Grin and Bear It
6.plot: Rick and Andrew get a taste of animal transportation down under when they move a rescued kangaroo and her joey across Texas. Meanwhile, Justin and Ashley venture into the labyrinth of a dark cattle farm to find, wrangle and move a pair of imposing and aggressive warthogs.

8.title: Liger for Life
8.plot: Rick and Andrew are tasked with transporting two gigantic ligers from Massachusetts to South Carolina. The massive feline cargo proves to be the least of their worries as the miles catch up to their trusty transport vehicle. Meanwhile, Justin and Ashley get their feathers ruffled while trying to load up two very large ostriches.

-1.title: Dude Where's My Giraffe
-1.plot: A giraffe is transported by Rick and Andrew in the Season 1 finale. Later, Justin and Ashley haul two African cranes and a black leopard.

imdb.plot outline: If you've got dangerous and deadly animals to move, you need the crew at Florida-based Wild Transport. Meet Rick DeRidder and Andrew Biddle, who hit back roads and highways with unique and potentially deadly cargo in tow. From anacondas to zedonks, these guys transport large mammals, reptiles and raptors of all kinds.If you've got dangerous and deadly animals to move, you need the crew at Florida-based Wild Transport.
